European powers call for ‘strong security guarantees’ for Ukraine European powers on Wednesday called for “strong security guarantees” for Ukraine and said that any negotiation with Russia must include both Ukraine and Europe. “We are looking forward to discussing the way ahead together with our American allies. Our shared objectives should be to put Ukraine in a position of strength,” wrote France, Britain, Germany, Poland, Italy, Spain and the European Union in a statement. The pointed pledge of support came hours after President Donald Trump appeared to affirm Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth’s line that Ukraine’s stated goal of reclaiming its full internationally recognized territory was “unrealistic.” Trump spoke by phone on Wednesday with Russian President Vladimir Putin in their first publicized call since Trump returned to the White House.
